ygData.messageBody:
Heh.

That hole is huge. If you swim down far enough you hit... NOTHING! I even
scraped the walls to see if I could find a secret room, nothing. Anywho. I
scanned all of Ak'anon today underwater (145 swimming currently). Didn't see
anything cool to note. Scanned for about an hour or so. Was a waste of time I
think.

-Kryogen Katspaw

--- Tony Buser <gr0k@...> wrote:
> Well I hate to say it, but it wasn't much of a clue. I mean... there's a
> LOT of water in the game. Could be anywhere.
>
> Though one time I thought there might be something under all that water in
> ak'anon and I swam around all one day. Didn't find anything. I did find a
> place where you can swim behind the wall out in front of the mines where the
> Necro guild is, but I drowned and had to call a gm to get my corpse out.
> Maybe I'll see if I can find someone to cast endureing breath so I can
> search in there more fully.
